      "title": "CPC gains from petrol, super diesel; incurs losses from auto diesel, kerosene",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With the increase of\u00a0 Ceylon Petroleum Corporation (CPC) fuel prices from early this morning, the estimated cost of imported refined petroleum products was released by the Power and Energy Minister.",
        "Accordingly, the Ceylon Petroleum Corparation (CPC) will gain a profit of Rs. 68.61 from a litre of Octane 95 petrol and Rs. 15.57 on Octane 92 and also it gains Rs. 20.27 from super diesel.",
        "However, the CPC incurs a loss of Rs. 8.52 from a litre of auto diesel and Rs. 334 per litre of kerosene. (Darshana Sanjeewa Balasuriya)"
      ],
